aa(lp188
VBefore I close, though, let me tell you about my grandmother.
p189
aVShe grew up at a time when Confucianism was the social norm
p190
aVand the local mandarin was the person who mattered.
p191
aVLife hadn't changed for centuries.
p192
aVHer father died soon after she was born.
p193
aVHer mother raised her alone.
p194
aVAt 17, she became the second wife of a mandarin whose mother beat her.
p195
aVWith no support from her husband,
p196
aVshe caused a sensation by taking him to court
p197
aVand prosecuting her own case,
p198
aVand a far greater sensation when she won.
p199
